      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "8 Abel—Byrd's MONETTE"
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        322,
        224,
        846,
        253
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=1067,742,1735,96",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "PARTY LINE AND EXTENSION TELEPHONE HINTS"
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        193,
        282,
        977,
        309
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=639,935,2597,89",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "EFFICIENT PARTY LINE SERVICE depends largely on the consideration and courtesy which each subscriber gives to the other parties on his line. Endeavor to limit your calls to five minutes duration."
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        194,
        358,
        977,
        384
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=643,1186,2593,87",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "When dialing on a party line, or any line with an extension telephone, it is necessary to consider the possibility that someone else may be using the line. Learn and observe the following rules and be a courteous party line neighbor:"
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        218,
        416,
        575,
        434
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=722,1379,1183,59",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "1. If you hear a conversation when lifting the receiver, the line is being used. Replace the receiver and try the call again later."
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        240,
        579,
        576,
        603
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=795,1919,1113,79",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "2. If you hear the sound of \"Dialing Clicks\" when lifting the receiver, it means that someone else on the line is dialing a number. The lifting of your receiver has interfered with the dialing and you should inform him to dial the number again. Hang up your receiver and permit him to dial the number again."
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        240,
        602,
        576,
        622
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=795,1995,1113,66",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "3. If you are dialing and hear another party lift his receiver before you have heard the \"Ringing Signal,\" inform him that the line is in use and after he has replaced his receiver, replace your own for a few moments. Then remove it and dial the complete number again."
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        240,
        641,
        577,
        665
      ],
      "canvas_fragment": "https://www.loc.gov/item/usteledirec01083/canvas/15#xywh=795,2124,1116,80",
      "confidence": "line",
      "gemini_text": "4. When another party lifts his receiver after you have heard the \"Ringing Signal,\" it will not be necessary to redial the number. Merely inform him that the line is in use."
    },
    {
      "bbox": [
        339,
        717,
